          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 3,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " for more Nintendo Switch content. Also, please consider ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 3,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "supporting us on Patreon",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "__GHOST_URL__/cyber-shadow-switch-review/Patreon.com/switchaboo",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 3,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " so that we can continue to keep the website running and get our fortnightly podcast two days early.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "But, why? Sure, nicer graphics, smoother gameplay, and maybe even a bigger screen ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "all ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "sound good, but what does that actually look like when you apply it to other titles? Well, take for instance the render distance of ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The Legend of Zelda: Breath of the Wild - ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "the game is beautiful, no doubting that, but imagine being able to see the distant landscapes with even better visual fidelity - eye watering. Or, imagine the potential for other games to be ported like ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Red Dead Redemption 2",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ". It's currently somewhat of a headache getting your title to run smoothly on a Switch, which is why you don't see every single new triple-A title bothering to come to the platform. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Call of Duty",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " isn't on the main store, neither is",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " Cyberpunk 2077",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ", and ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Hitman 3 ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "relies on internet-based cloud streaming (something most internet connections aren't ready for, and something some regions can't even use yet), but picture having these new titles alongside the likes of Mario, Zelda, Pok√©mon, Animal Crossing, and all the other flagship titles that ultimately sell Nintendo as a brand. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "So, it'd be good, benefit the consumer, definitely cost more, but it's idealistic, a pipe dream... right? No, not exactly. You see, the Switch the way it is now is because of Nvidia, that sparkly gaming brand that make graphics cards for PC that let you have next-gen lighting techniques and play all your games in ultra graphics if you fork out the cash, and guess what they did in 2020? They made a pro version of their Shield TV and it got ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "rave ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "reviews. To top it off, there's tech in the first party games that utilise dynamic resolution, and these would automatically be upscaled to 4k, meaning that you could enjoy the fruits of ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Breath of the Wild",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " in a crisper resolution.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "src": "__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2021/03/image-22.png",
        "width": 1921,
        "height": 1081,
        "caption": "Image Credit: IGN"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "When you look at the PlayStation 5 and Xbox Series X, you see exciting potential in new features, new possibilities. Ray-tracing is likely out of the question given the desire to make the Switch a handheld system too - something that absolutely should be retained - but even Xbox saw the adaptive triggers of the new PlayStation controllers and found themselves jealous. Nintendo doesn't compete with the others, that's known - it's always been that way - but to say the Switch didn't learn anything from the gaming market as it is today would be to lie plainly, so why shouldn't it improve its controllers to boot? That drift is ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "horrendous, ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "they could do with a little more weight, maybe be a little nicer to hold, and they definitely could utilise the likes of haptic feedback and adaptive triggers. All in all, the Pro model could ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "add ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "a lot of new features, but why stop there? It could also refine and perfect what's already there - after all, Nintendo is facing lawsuit after lawsuit with its god-awful drift.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "embed",
        "url": "https://open.spotify.com/episode/2kBdVhgxFiWvbsefB77aUV?si=a_e7_dMrQzSUYoPAB8qCfw",
        "html": "<iframe width=\"100%\" height=\"232\" allowtransparency=\"true\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"encrypted-media\" title=\"Spotify Embed: The Switchaboo Name That Game Spectacular\" src=\"https://open.spotify.com/embed-podcast/episode/2kBdVhgxFiWvbsefB77aUV?si=a_e7_dMrQzSUYoPAB8qCfw\"></iframe>",
        "metadata": {
          "width": 600,
          "height": 232,
          "version": "1.0",
          "provider_name": "Spotify",
          "provider_url": "https://spotify.com/",
          "title": "The Switchaboo Name That Game Spectacular",
          "thumbnail_url": "https://i.scdn.co/image/ab67656300005f1f43f01249339943f69a680a91",
          "thumbnail_width": 300,
          "thumbnail_height": 300
        },
        "embedType": "rich"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "For now, we have the upcoming new Switch model which gives us a bigger screen. Sure, it's a step up, and that's great, but a native 4k home menu and some new Pro features to boot would be nice. As it stands, Samsung's new screen feels like a taster, one I'd rather not invest in since it's probably best just to wait for the hypothetical that ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "might ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "happen. Is it likely? Well, it's a maybe. Publicly, they deny it at every turn, but behind the scenes? There's lots to indicate something is in the works. It wouldn't have to compete with the other giants either, as it could simply be a means to get more games on the store while also improving their own titles - it doesn't have to be next-gen, as stated earlier, just Nintendo's own step forward, and wouldn't that be swell? ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
